content: Great app. Better than Domino's proprietary app. Wish it could pull info from there so didn't have to duplicate, but best for keeping track of your tips and mileage. Didn't really need pro features but paid for it just to show support.
replyContent: I'm glad you like it! If there were a way to pull in that data, I certainly would do it. Unfortunately, the only way to do it would be if Domino's provided a method for accessing it (they never will). Also, it's against their app's ToS to attempt to harvest any data from it.

content: Love it. It does a better job at navigation than the app I have to use for my job. I was going to suggest a tip calculator for cash payments until I realized it's already in there. My only complaint is that no matter what I say with the voice tool, it seems to put it into the address, even if I say "tip equals" beforehand. Definitely not a big deal though. I can work with that. NOTE: I was saying it wrong. The tip thing works if you say "tip amount equals". So, yeah, even better.
replyContent: I'm glad you like it! For entering prepaid tips, you have to say "tip amount equals". I originally was using "tip equals", but it kept getting misinterpreted by the speech recognizer. You can check out all the voice commands by pressing the "VOICE HELP" button from in the app or by going here: https://gavingt.github.io/voice-input-instructions.html

content: This app does everything. Only drawback is that you can't do split pay hourly.
Great app, very useful for keeping track of income and tips
Super cool app! I'd pay extra for more reporting features!
replyContent: I'm glad you like it! More features are coming soon, and at no additional cost :)

content: If you deliver, this app is perfect.
great app for Domino's, very clean and many QoL features
Good functions but I lost a whole days worth of deliveries and tips when I upgraded to pro, not happy with that because it was over $100.
replyContent: When I first released the app in 2014, Android didn't yet have the ability to make in-app purchases. So allowing a user to upgrade from Free to Pro and maintain all their app data wasn't possible. And to make it work now, I'd need to release an entirely new app. So the Free version simply doesn't store shift history. Sorry for the inconvenience!

content: I've used this app for over a year, and it has been a pleasure to use and is far superior to the Domino's Driver app.
First of all, I never buy apps. I've been using android phones for about 15 years, and I've only bought about four or five. I used the trial app for three days, and bought this one.
Friggin love this app. Best app for delivery drivers.
Fantastic app for any delivery driver. Written by someone who delivers pizza it's kind of focused on that but I'm sure it will work for other types of deliveries.
Once I got past the learning curve it was okay. Started Uber in April I wish I could have put in some of those past. Great job.
replyContent: I'm glad it's working for you. Allowing users to add previously completed shifts is a feature I have on my to-do list.

content: Everything works amazing! The one suggestion I would have is the option to add previous shifts to provide the history I already have. I wish I discovered this sooner! I've been stuck with paper and pen and it was so time consuming!
replyContent: Thanks! That's a feature I would like to add when I get some more time to work on the app.

content: Thanks for the update! So I make 1.20 per delivery with one of the locations I work at, but .23 cents per miles at another. Is there any way to assign these to each location, or do I need to switch it back and forth?
replyContent: Currently, you do have to manually switch back and forth. I hope to add a "Store profile" option in the future for quickly switching between stores with different mileage rates. It'll be something I prioritize when I have more time to work on the app. Thanks!

content: Strongly recommend for my fellow pizza deliverators.
Great way to track my tip and I learned you can pre set up an order

Update: Thanks for getting back so quick.......I will give it another shot tonight and maybe I'll change my mind and review. Thank you There's a few issues for me. The phone number having to be put in bothers me and also for someone driving constantly it's a lot of data with to many options needed to enter while on the road. Maybe just make it way more basic so I can talk to text it instead of needing to look down.
replyContent: You can enter as little or as much info as you want. Phone numbers are only required if you want to save customer order history (addresses are not enough to uniquely identify customers). If you only enter tips, the app will automatically find delivery addresses and calculate driving distances. Also, there are voice commands for entering info.

content: Love this app and wondering if it will be available on my iPhone to use.
replyContent: Glad you like it! Sorry, no iPhone version for the foreseeable future. I'm working to become a professional Android developer, so I'm focused purely on Android right now.

content: This app is amazing at keeping track of how much I get throughout my shift and how much I owe the store. Takes out all the math and guesswork. I recommend 100%
Nice,,,better
Absolutely love this app!!

Not sure if it's my phone or the app but it will not allow me to pin the short cut to my home screen. This is this only issue I have run into. If this is an issue with my phone please let me know and I will remove this review (I have already posted a 5 star review). Thanks!!
replyContent: I've never heard of that happening before. It sounds like an issue with your phone's launcher app, though. My app doesn't have control over what happens on the home screen. I guess it's possible that you have the Free and Pro versions both on your home screen, and your launcher app doesn't allow you to have two apps both called "Tips" at once?

content: Fantastic app. Definitely worth the bucks. Highly recommend this for anyone wanting to organize their deliveries and gain a statistical perspective as well, provided all information is accurate.
Love this app only have two problems with it one. It doesn't keep track of actual order numbers. To it doesn't keep track of split pay. Other than that, I love the app
replyContent: Order numbers are something I'll support in the near future. Split pay is harder because I would have to either 1) keep the app always running to check when you return to the store, or 2) force user to hit a button every time they enter/leave the store. So instead I recommend you find your average hourly pay rate from your paycheck and use that.

content: I absolutely love this app, it keeps track of basically everything I need. My only gripe is that I can't store an order number with each delievery. It would be really helpful to be able to glance back at an order and know what order number belonged to it.
replyContent: I'm glad you like it! Order numbers are something I want to add in the future. I would have to add another row of buttons to accommodate it. And adding more buttons makes filling out upcoming orders more difficult, so it's a trade-off that I'll have to consider going forward.

content: Absolutely amazing! Does everything you need in multiple ways. Perfect app so far

I really enjoy this app, but only the premium version. I understand keeping some features locked to encourage payment, but I didn't feel like I was gaining anything with the free version. that being said, the premium version is a very reasonable price considering what other apps charge. the only thing I really wish is that pulling up a saved customer's profile was easier to access once it loads their number/address, since I keep gate codes, requests, and reminders in the customer notes
replyContent: The easiest way to access a customer profile is to enter their phone number using the "Customer phone number" button on the main screen, then click on the button and select "Customer profile". I considered putting this information directly on the main screen, but it would have been too cluttered.

content: Won't accept the answers to get thru the set up paid 3.00 for nothing
replyContent: I'll need more information, as this hasn't been a problem for any other users. Please email me at gavingt@gmail.com and we'll figure it out.

content: Great app! Please add the option to edit order dates and times and ability to add orders for past shifts for 5 stars
replyContent: This is something that would actually take a ton of code rewriting, as various parts of the app rely on orders to be entered in chronological order. I'd like to fix this at some point though.

content: Fantastic App, easy to use, great functionality, highly recommend

This is acceptable with one suggestion. I am paid 8% of each order I deliver and would like to see that option implemented into this app. For now, I can at least mentally do the math and add that to the tip. Otherwise, this app is perfect.
replyContent: That's on my list of things to add, as soon as I get more time to work on the app. I've just been swamped with real life matters lately.

content: Love the app. Paid for the pro version and it works perfectly, maybe a couple tweaks but it's an awesome app.
Great!

Stellar app! I am so incredibly impressed with this app! It keeps everything I need for all my deliveries right here! There is a small learning curve but once you get used to using this app you will wonder how you EVER got by without it. It's so organized, streamlined and keeps everything you need right at your fingertips. I love how I can see my nightly breakdown in several ways. I can go back and see how someone paid to make sure my numbers are correct. Thank you for creating this amazing app
Is there a way to remember people who stiff and alert me when its them so I can deprioritize their delivery?
replyContent: If you enter customer phone numbers, their average tip amount will show up at the bottom of the screen any time you enter their phone number. If you're only entering addresses and not phone numbers, you can also use the "Nearby orders" feature to see what people at that address tip.

content: So far I am really liking this app.I will give it the 5th Star on that rating if I can figure out how you keep track of your weekly as well as daily earnings.
replyContent: From the menu, select "Order history". Then select "View by day" at the bottom of the screen to switch to viewing by week, month, year, all-time, or a custom range. Hope that helps! Let me know if that works for you.

content: Not getting paid to say this. This app is awesome. Maybe the easiest app I've ever used as everything is spelled out for you. Literally. A+ in my book

I can't believe how perfect this app is!!! The creater had to have worked as a delivery driver for quite a while... It's virtually impossible that someone who hasn't done this kind of work would know EXACTLY what someone in this field wants and needs. Anyway, no matter how perfect an app is, if it's NOT easy to use, literally on-the-fly, it would be WORTHLESS!! What makes it GENIUS is how easy it is to enter data. I tried the free version first, and immediately realized that $2.99 is a steal!!!
replyContent: I'm really glad you like it! Also, you're right. I've been a driver for 12 years now :O

content: Great app!

Super helpful app! The only thing missing is tracking split wages. Please consider adding this? I don't mind having to push a button every time I leave and get back, or keeping the app open if it means accurately tracking my wages.
Get the pro- 10000000% worth it. And it's so good to support this developer. It's such a clever app.

I absolutely love this app because is tracks everything I need it to! Prior to using this app I was tracking everything on a paper that I came up with myself. My old GM actually found this app for me after I showed him how I track my tips and mileage. I have really bad OCD and can't deviate from keeping all of the information but it's very time consuming so this app saves a lot of time! I started out with the free version but decided to download the paid one because it saves information.

Fantastic app, best tip tracker app by FAR. Even has a voice input function that automatically inputs addresses and navigates to them, and also enters your tip amount as well. Tracks separate entries such as mileage, hourly wage, tips etc. Wish I would have found this long ago. Well worth the small one time fee. Would give it more stars if I could. Thank you for making life just as bit easier.
awesome it does nearly everything I could want it to do only possible option I could see as an improvement would be a split wage for differing pays when inside the store and on the road
replyContent: The problem with tracking split wage is the app would need to know every time you enter/exit the store. This would require either pressing a button or the app always running (draining lots of battery). So I recommend that you look at your paychecks and divide your earnings by your hours worked to find an average hourly rate. This works well for me.

content: Perfect app I'm a dominos driver and it fits perfect for dominos
Great app! The only thing that would make it perfect was if it had the ability to track split pay for in store rate vs on the road rate
replyContent: The problem with tracking split wage is the app would need to know every time you enter/exit the store. This would require either pressing a button or the app always running (draining lots of battery). So I recommend that you look at your paychecks and divide your earnings by your hours worked to find an average hourly rate. This works well for me.

content: Works very well, great replacement for Delivery Droid
Loved this app from the beginning been using it ever since. Great way to keep track of tips, millage reimbursement and regular customers. Developer answers questions and concerns promptly
replyContent: The problem with tracking split wage is the app would need to know every time you enter/exit the store. This would require either pressing a button or the app always running (draining lots of battery). So I recommend that you look at your paychecks and divide your earnings by your hours worked to find an average hourly rate. This works well for me.

content: The app works great and I enjoyed it a lot. But it does have one flaw. My mileage is based upon a percentage of the dollar amount that I deliver. There is currently no option for that right now.
replyContent: That's a mileage setup I've not heard of before. How does it work exactly? Does a higher order price mean more mileage or less?

content: Excellent app for tracking wages and tips. Been using this for over a year and its really come in handy.
Easy to use

Pretty nice app, overall. However, there's definitely room for improvement. Address autocomplete is basically useless; it usually doesn't even pop up until the address is fully entered. Sometimes after entering an address, it'll change itself to a similar address that is well outside my delivery zone, so I have enter my zip code to force it to use the proper address. There doesn't appear to be a way to view past shifts, which is a feature I'd expect this app to have. Other than that, great app.
replyContent: Google started charging ridiculous fees to use their address autocomplete functionality, so I was forced to use a free solution instead. I'm constantly working to improve the results so that the things you mention happen less often. Also, past shifts can be viewed by going to the menu and selecting "Order history".

content: This is a very time consuming app. I mean if you have the time to do it it would be great. But I need a simpler app for what I'm doing.
replyContent: You can enter as much or as little information as you want. If you choose to only enter the tip amounts, the app will find addresses and driving distances automatically from your GPS. Also, voice commands make entering information a lot faster.

content: Very nice app, hoping an update will include a different color font for cash tips versus credit card tips on the main screen.
replyContent: Thanks for the suggestion. This would definitely be easier than flipping back and forth through the pages on the main screen to view the "Tip pay method" column.

content: Great app. All it takes is a couple of seconds to put in information before each run and you end up with really detailed information about almost anything related to delivering.

If possible, to have the option to set desired time after the start of shift before we can go on break, so that we don't clock out early and have an early break violation. And if you work pass certain hours, (minus break time) to calculate o.t. also, like a pause option, with timer, for lunch break,so I can know my exact times and earnings for each day, also not clock in early/late from break. And maybe some how incorporate a way to track of pay periods, wk/bi-wkly
replyContent: I'm glad you like it! I'll be adding support for breaks and pay periods in a future update. And I'll certainly consider the other features you mention. I do worry about adding too many features and confusing users. But if there's enough demand for something and I have time to do it, I'll try my best to add it.

content: Love this app! I would love to have a shift comments section to be included in the history. It would be helpful to make notes about the shift (weather conditions, number of drivers, special events going on). Also i would prefer of you would separate the mileage reimbursement from the wages earned because it is not a wage.
replyContent: I do have plans for a shift comments feature in the future, so look out for that. Also, I plan to allow the user to change the "Earnings" number that shows up on the main screen to instead show "Tips" or "Pre-wage earnings".  Hopefully that addresses your second request.

content: I really love this app. I use it all the time for work. The only problem I have is I bought an iPhone and this app is unavailable through Apple. Sooo... I have to use my old phone to continue using my app so I dont have all the options. Please make this app available through Apple. Thank you
replyContent: I'm glad you like it. I'm squarely focused on Android at the moment because I'm trying to get a job as a professional Android developer. But maybe at some point in the future I'll have time to make an iOS version.

content: Basically a perfect app, dev thought of EVERYTHING related to delivery driving. Things I'd like to see added: •Automatic standard bank option (instead of adding a negative transaction every work day) •An easier way to do a split tip [(cash given with a tip on credit card also) similar to how the split payment works] I'm nitpicking there though, greatest app ever, love the customer base, crazy amounts of stats and quality of life it adds to work.
replyContent: I added a "Starting bank" option in the most recent beta build. The beta program is open for anyone to join by visiting the app's store page. As for adding split tips, you can use the "Prepaid tip amount" option to specify cash and credit tip amounts. It's not super intuitive but it works until I figure out a better solution.  Hope that helps!

content: I am brand new(2 weeks) at delivery driving along with the store I just started at has just started delivery. This app is great for keeping track of orders to compare with the computers at the end of shift. It is also great to know if this new job is worth the wear and tear it puts on my vehicle.
This app is *still* a must-have for all delivery drivers.
Awesome app a must for all delivery drivers I just reset my phone and can't figure out how to get my old deliveries back that I had prior. Do I need to be signed on with specific Google account ?
replyContent: I'm glad you like it! If you made a backup file before you reset the phone, I can guide you through how to restore it. Android is supposed to automatically back up app data, but it can fail sometimes. That's why the app periodically reminds you to make a backup file.

content: everything I knew I wanted plus more. Love it!
outstanding performance

I really like this app. I used to use Tip Jar, which is gone now, but it wasn't geared towards delivery. One thing I'd like to see is split pay. A lot of corporate stores are paying more in the store to avoid law suits. That's the only reason I gave it 4. I can't accurately see how much money I made during the shift. Also, how about pay periods start to end? These would be helpful to creating a budget.
replyContent: To track split pay the user would need to press a button every time they leave/enter the store. This would be a hassle. Instead, I recommend finding your average hourly pay by dividing your paycheck amount by your hours worked. Use that for 'Hourly pay rate'. In my experience, this number is pretty stable over time. Also I like the pay period idea.

content: awesome!!!!
Awesome app!! Makes it so much easier to keep track of things. Plus, I love all the data it effortlessly keeps.
this app is bad ass !!!

works great though i dont recommend using automileage. it is way off from actual mileage..i wish it had a means of accommodating wage variations. i get one rate while at the store and a different rate while on the road. edit: we generally do only take single runs but my automileage was off by over $5. i just use beginning and ending mileage per shift. i wouldnt mind a setting that automatically adjusts pay when on a run. may be able to hash out a method if interested.
replyContent: Make sure you're using the 'Orders in progress' button when you're taking more than 1 run, or else the app will think you're only taking singles. Also I didn't want the user to have to clock in/clock out every time they leave/enter the store, so I recommend just using an average of the two wages. Email me at gavingt@gmail.com to discuss more.

content: awesome app love it

I just used the free version tonight and its awesome. In fact so awesome i paid for the pro. I only have one issue and that is the pro isnt bringing up the data in the free version. Is that data lost, or can i import it in to the pro? Thanks!
replyContent: Glad you like it! Unfortunately, the free version doesn't save any data beyond the current shift. Perhaps I'll change this in the future so that the data can be imported to the pro version. Sorry about that!

content: delivering pizzas for 28 years and I can safely say I love this app! one suggestion that I would like to see you add in your next update would be having some kind of a spot on each shift to be able to make notes. something like big festival in town for any kind of notes that would tell you some more information about why the shift was the way it was. weather conditions how many drivers were working that kind of stuff just general notes that I can put into document in my shift better
replyContent: Thanks! That's definitely something I'll look into adding in the future.

content: amazing app. easy to use.

Love the app & the new updates! However 1 more thing to add to new days of week feature is how many of those days of the week have we worked, ex. I usually thurs thru sun, but sometimes work other days, what's the total count for each day of week, (25 sundays/2 weds) Maybe a new feature could be, the best part of the month, ex. 1st or 15th or 25th
replyContent: Thanks for the suggestions. As of the most recent release, the chart now excludes days of the week with proportionally small "Hours worked". Also, clicking on the chart now shows a table that includes a column for "Hours worked". I'll consider your other suggestion as I move forward.

content: great app would give 5 but cant do by mile and order at same time like my store pays by the mile but after 9pm we get an extra dollar per run
replyContent: There are some technical reasons that would make this complicated for me to implement. But I'd like to support every store's mileage system, so I'll definitely keep this in mind as I continue working on the app. Thanks!

content: eFFeN AWESOME!

if you deliver you really should use this app so you can view your earnings and keep track of everything from miles to hourly rate including tips that you made that day, week, month or however you want to look at your indormation. especially if you work nights and dont have time to manage all this yourself. Great tool for assessing your financials. This is legit af the best $3 I have ever spent.
excellent the only problem is you can't transfer info when you change phones
replyContent: You can transfer your info. On your old phone, go to the 'Settings' menu in the app, then 'Manage data', then select 'Generate database backup file'. This will create a backup file which you can restore on your new phone. Email me at gavingt@gmail.com if you need help with this.

content: love this app. is there any way you could set up a Split shift like i work 11-1 5-9 but i hate having to end one shift and start another!
replyContent: Glad you like it! I'll look into this and see if there's a way to implement it that makes sense.

content: I've been a delivery driver for almost 5 years and this app is a lifesaver! I'm impressed with all the features, especially being able to sort by day, week, month, year, or all time to view a history of my tips. The app is frequently updated, and often when I load it up I'll see new features have been added.  At the end of every shift I know exactly what I'll owe to the store and what I'll be taking home, which has helped my sanity tremendously instead of trying to keep it all written out on paper.  If you're a delivery driver, you need this app! The paid version is well worth it!
this app have made my delivery experience so much more smooth. and makes nightky count out a breeze
It would be nice to have an in-app feature that could produce a route for multiple deliveries.
replyContent: The "Orders in progress" screen lets you view all your upcoming orders on a map. This can help you decide the best route and adjust it accordingly. However, providing automatic route optimization would require me to use Google's "Distance Matrix" service. But this would cost me thousands of dollars each month and I'd go bankrupt. So I just can't :(

content: this tip tracker is the best one I've used.
works great! accurate, fast and helpful!
Very handy app. One change to request: Please add an option for Kilometers for tracking mileage.
replyContent: I've just added support for kilometers to the beta release. You can join the beta and get it now or wait a couple weeks for it to be available to everyone. Thanks for the feedback.

content: Amazing app for delivery drivers. Seriously, if you drive delivery buy this app. You won't regret it. So powerful.
Been using this to deliver pizzas for years. The pro version is a bargain.
I love this app. Adding tips is so easy. the only thing i would change is having the mileage added separately from the tips
replyContent: Thanks! Feel free to send me an email and expand on what you mean about the mileage. I'm not sure if you want to add a custom mileage value for each order (already possible) or if you want to add a total mileage value at the end of your shift (technically possible if you just set your mileage rate to 0 and then edit a single order's mileage).

content: amazing, easy to use, and the creator of said app is always keeping in touch with us to let us know about changes to the app. As a delivery driver, I highly reccomend this app.
Worth 2.99! Keeps track of deliveries, mileage, and tips, as well as total earnings. Highly recommend!

absolutely love using this app. the only problem I have with it is, when I create a spreadsheet for backup, it doesnt show on the sheet the actual date/day for each delivery. it shows the 'timestamp' but that looks more like a cryptic number than an actual date.
replyContent: "timestamp" is Unix time in milliseconds. The "formattedTimeAndDate" shows both the time and date, but it's not obvious because the date is actually on the second line. Double-click on of the cells in this column and it should expand to show the date. EDIT: I've fixed this in the latest beta release. Both time and date now show on one line.

content: great for pizza drivers. but for uber or doordash need to be able not have home location.
I love this app for keeping track of my deliveries. I wish you could select the app you call from.
replyContent: I'm glad you like it. The app is set up so that it will open your default dialer app, or prompt you to select one if you don't have a default already chosen. I tested this out with a few different dialers and it worked as intended, but feel free to email me if you're having any problems with it.

content: not as fluent as I would like, i bought the app and i still refer to Google search and writing down my deliveries
replyContent: Let me know if you're having issues with the app not recognizing specific addresses. That's something I'm constantly iterating on because Google's database isn't perfect. But the app's basic functionality doesn't differ between Free and Pro.

content: Wonderful program that just keeps getting better with every update!
love the app so far only had for week or 2 only wish it would rotate
replyContent: I'm glad you like it! I'll get around to implementing landscape mode eventually. It's actually a lot of work so I'm focusing on other things first.

content: Love it near perfect app use it everyday (I am a delivery driver) only request would be a way to put multiple addresses into Google at once dunno if possible and only bug I see is when I pick address from map always overrides first order when multi order is chosen even when selecting from 2nd or 3rd order.
replyContent: I assume you mean entering multiple stops at once into Google Maps navigation. Unfortunately they haven't exposed this functionality to developers yet. As for the bug, I've got it fixed and I'll release it to you guys as soon as I wrap up some other improvements. Thanks!

content: This is a cool app! Love the database feature and all the great stats and data I can see about my deliveries. Is recommend to any delivery driver! Almost everything you need to be smarter about your job is right here.

great app, I wish it would save by the address without having to worry about the name or phone number, as that info isnt relevant for some drivers. paid for the pro and havent been disappointed, it would.just be nice to be able to see past deliveries tons certain address without having to save by phone number or name.
replyContent: The app uses phone numbers to identify customers because addresses aren't unique identifiers. For instance, an apartment complex can have one address but thousands of residents. But you can still search past orders by address. Just go to Search, click the 'Search type' button in the top-right, and select "Find an order by address". Hope that helps!

content: does evwrything i could want it to do. vwry hapltand have used it for about a year now. my only request after using it for so ling is that it would be great if there was a boz to write down order number. have worked at 2 different atorea and they both track your deliveries usong order number so i am still writing on a piece od paper each delivery order number. would love when its time to cash out to just walk up with my phone and have all the info i need. otherwise i love everything aboit the app
replyContent: Let me think about the best way to add an 'order numbers' feature. My main concern is finding a place to put it.

content: I accidentally deleted my pro edition , is there any way of getting it back?
replyContent: I'm guessing you uninstalled the app or deleted the app data. If you created a backup file from within the app, you can restore it. I recommend making occasional backups. The app also uses Android auto-backup, which should restore your app data assuming it's configured correctly on your device.

content: great app! only issue i have is the amount owed to store is not calculated correctly. also a option to put what the store gives you to make change (the bank) would be great.
replyContent: I've fixed the "amount owed to store" calculation and added a "cash drops" feature, along with tons of other stuff. You can enter a bank as a negative cash drop. So if your banks are $20, enter -20. Thanks for the feedback!

content: Help! Wages per hour? I purchased the pro version. I am paid $1.00 per delivery. I am paid $7.25 per hour also.   EDITING after reply from Gavin's App Creations:    Your reply makes perfect sense. My employer does split two different amounts inside and on the road. Yes, it would be a pain to keep up with it each time. Instead, I can just write down my time on the delivery tags and calculate it all at the end of the night, minus my shift clock in and clock out.  Thank you for getting back with this so quickly!
replyContent: I haven't added this because most chains now use a "split pay" system, where drivers get paid one rate on the road and another in-store. So they'd have to hit a button every time they entered/exited the store, which is just too much in my opinion. Geofencing isn't a viable solution for this either due to new limitations in Android.

content: love it.

Great app works perfectly, very convenient. Also has a map built in now to oversee your runs which is very helpful for doubles and triples, etc. Now there is a navigate back to store button which was the only thing I felt the app was lacking. Its great to keep track of all my money and build a database of the customers and have a history of their tips and what not. Best app of its kind for sure! Developer is awesome and very helpful if you ever have an issue! 6 stars!!

This is an amazing app that I use almost daily for delivery work delivering pizza and it is nearly flawless, the only things that I feel the app is lacking is the ability to rearrange orders once you have multiple ones typed in already as well as a quick way or an automatic way for the GPS to auto route you back to your shop after all deliveries have been finished. Sometimes I get turned around in areas I have not been and will just then have to open my GPS, or activate my Google Assistant to get me home. Not a huge deal but it would be convenient if the app had a feature to just automatically route you back. Never had a single issue with the app like I said nearly flawless keep up the great work!!
replyContent: You can actually rearrange orders using the vertical dot buttons underneath each upcoming order. This gives you the option to swap with the above or below order. An option to navigate back to the store sounds like something I could add. Maybe look out for that in the next update.

content: Excellent app I love the new interface looks great!
I love this app. The free version does a well enough job but the Pro version is well worth the money. Very happy to have found this.
Brilliant tool for all kinds of delivery drivers. Pro features definitely worth the buy!
Greatest

Using the new updated app, sooo much better than previous version, I would like to suggest a few things if you don't mind.... with cash orders have it subtract the amount of cash given minus the total and have that full in the tip line... add in a section for order numbers, it'd be easier to look up than addresses... and lastly when you have multiple orders the ability to look at a map and see where they are sort of like the tip map.... loving the new updates and can't wait to see what else you come up with
replyContent: If you enter an order price and then use the Calculator button from the 'Add a tip" screen, it'll automatically fill in the order price you entered. Order numbers are something I could add but didn't figure anyone would want to fuss with. Viewing all orders in progress on a map is a great idea and I'll definitely be adding it. Thanks!

content: This app is a must-have for delivery drivers. Love it. Lets me track my mileage, tips and order history all at once
Best tip tracking app I've used!
Awesome

Amazing app! Thanks so much for the reply last time. I know you have a lot in the works, I think a "screen always on" feature would be very handy too. Highly recommend this to any delivery drivers out there, it does absolutely everything you need it to, and is continuously getting even better!

I've been using the free version for a long time. The upgrades to the latest version address nearly every issue I had with the app. I'm more than happy to lay down the small amount of money for the Pro version. Buy this app and support Gavin!
replyContent: Thanks, that means a lot! Sorry it took so long to bring this app into the modern age.

content: This is hands down the best tip tracker app on the play store. It is very user friendly and has all the features you will need as a delivery driver.
Super legit. Bought pro after my first shift using free. I love everything about it.
Nice and simple UI. The calculation was dead on at the end of the night. I love all the extra features!
I had been Using. For a 3 year and this has been the best upgrade look

Been using this app for over a year and I really love the resign you've done to it. The built in calculator is a nice QoL addition, the tip map was something I didn't know I wanted but now love, and having cents only in multiples of 5 was annoying in the prev version so I'm glad that's changed. This might be nick picky, but perhaps move the "Tip payment method" option into the "Add a tip" menu. Sometimes I find myself forgetting to switch the option so I have to back out just to change it. Is backing up straight to the Google cloud no longer an option, which was present in the old version? And speaking of back up maybe have the option to auto backup every time you hit end shift. Split screen support would be also nice to have but not necessary.
replyContent: I removed Backup to Google Cloud in favor of doing local backups. It was actually costing me money every time someone used it. I'll look into storing backups straight to the user's Google Drive, as that's free to use. I like the idea of auto-backups, but that poses some real technical challenges so I can't make any promises. Thanks!

content: It's the best. Ever.

replyContent: You can view your old order history data as a spreadsheet on your computer. I made the old version 6 years ago and I had no idea what I was doing. Unfortunately, the only way for me to make real improvements to the app was to keep the old order history data separate from the new.

content: Great way to track tips. Was always on point at the end of shift & saved me from losing money. Great tool.

It saves so much time and effort. I tried a couple others at the same time but none of them made it past day 1. This was by far the easiest to use and most accurate. Only issue I'm having is an "over query limit" message when it's attempting to pull an address, and having to type it in.   Really the best app purchase I've made in a long time.

content: I love this app! I would like to see a weekly tip review option instead of just monthly and daily. I would love that.

replyContent: The new version addresses all these points. Thanks for the feedback!

replyContent: Sure, I'll refund it. Just send me an email with your order number. App works great! Developer is very responsive to suggestions and bug fixes.

The inability to edit anything cripples this app please fix that. The main reason I had to uninstall was because of the mileage configuration, my restaurant uses a dynamic system where mileage fee is based on mileage. So 3 miles = $3, 20 =$20 and so on. replyContent: Tip amount editing and address editing is now in the newest version.  It's something I've been working on for a while.
